{
  "stem": "17426.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We traveled at night, until we came to the [INAUDIBLE], which is west of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there the Germans overran us, and we came back home.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mr.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Chmielinski was within two weeks arrested, as most of the intelligentsia were, and the rich Polish people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And his wife and son received his remains in a little box, the ashes.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there were proclamations and directives and laws that Jews are not allowed to do this and Jews are not allowed to do that.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Jews are not allowed to leave this town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Jews are-- there was a curfew at 7 o'clock-- only for Jews, not for Polish people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were making quite a distinction between Jews and Poles.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What they prohibited Jews, they still allowed Poles.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And with that, they wanted to get the support of Poles.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They did not want to antagonize the Polish people, so they could have them-- use them, so to speak, to possibly-- as instruments of destruction of their Jewish neighbors.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so they created a sort of a wall of understanding between Jews and non-Jews to the extreme.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They drove this so far, that Polish people were pointing out to them where Jews lived, so they could go in and they could plunder and they could beat and they could do whatever they wanted.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this is how it started.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My best friend, Szymon Treskawer, who went with me through school, my age.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I remember he was only a few days apart from my day of birth, as we often compared.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Also a member of the dramatic circle.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was hung in the center of town, just a few days before I even came back from Warsaw, we came back from Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was hung with 10 other citizens in Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Not only Jews.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
